===Etymology===
From the persian word در (dar) meaning court. Dari-persian means the Court-persian i.e. the standard Persian.

===Noun===
'''Dari-Persian'''
#A dialect of [[Persian]] spoken by a plurality of people in Afghanistan (68%). 
#A language of the Central Iranian family spoken by up to 15,000 people (mostly Zoroastrians) in the Yezd and Kerman areas.  Also known as [[Gabri]] or [[Gabar]]

